    1. Write code, which is compatible with Delphi 7-XE7 and FreePascal >= 3.0 *

  • so don't use generics/templates, operator overloading and another newer *

  • syntax features than Delphi 7 has support for that, but if needed, make *

  • it out-ifdef-able. *

    1. Don't use Delphi-only, FreePascal-only or Lazarus-only libraries/units, *

  • but if needed, make it out-ifdef-able. *

    1. No use of third-party libraries/units as possible, but if needed, make *

  • it out-ifdef-able. *

    1. Try to use const when possible. *

    1. Make sure to comment out writeln, used while debugging. *

    1. Make sure the code compiles on 32-bit and 64-bit platforms (x86-32, *

  • x86-64, ARM, ARM64, etc.). *
